    {
      "Text": "Security update for the Linux Kernel (Live Patch 41 for SLE 12 SP3)",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for the Linux Kernel 4.4.180-94_150 fixes one issue.\n\nThe following security issue was fixed:\n\n- CVE-2022-0330: A random memory access flaw was found in the Linux kernel's GPU i915 kernel driver functionality in the way a user may run malicious code on the GPU. This flaw allowed a local user to crash the system or escalate their privileges on the system. (bsc#1195950)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
